
Ann_Druyan
instance
Ann Druyan (/ˈdri.æn/ DREE-an; born June 13, 1949) is an American author and producer specializing in productions about cosmology and popular science. She was a co-writer of the 1980 PBS documentary series Cosmos, hosted by Carl Sagan (1934–1996), whom she married in 1981. She is the creator/producer/writer of the follow-up, Cosmos: A Spacetime Odyssey. She was in charge of music selections that were included with the pioneering spacecraft, Voyager 1 and Voyager 2.
